      <h1 class="display-1">Sales professional mortgage for the people whose income lives on the comp plan.</h1>
      <p class="lead hero-subtitle">Real estate agents, mortgage loan officers, insurance agents, pharma reps, software sales, financial advisors, and yacht brokers all share the same problem with generalist lenders: commission-driven income looks volatile on a tax return even when the pipeline is solid and the comp plan is signed. A promotion year breaks the two-year average. A slow quarter looks like decline. Stock comp doesn&rsquo;t show in W-2 wages. We read the comp plan, the W-2, the 1099, the pipeline letter, and the deferred-comp statement &mdash; and we qualify you on what you actually earn.</p>

      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call" class="btn btn-primary btn-large">Schedule a call with Jim</a>
        <a href="#professions" class="btn btn-secondary btn-large">Find your profession</a>
      </div>

      <div class="hero-trust">
        <span class="trust-dot"></span>
        <span>Broker NMLS #1072866</span>
        <span>&middot;</span>
        <span>Specialist in commission &amp; variable-income mortgages</span>
      </div>
        </div>
        <figure class="hero-image">
          <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/3760067/pexels-photo-3760067.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1200" alt="Sales professional in a modern office reviewing a contract with a client" loading="lazy" onerror="this.onerror=null;this.src='https://placehold.co/1200x1500/0A0E1A/E8EEFF/png?text=Sales+Professionals';">
